So the control flow issue is:- C: if awareness fails → maybe_fire → return (skip do_firing_stuff, skip visibility==2 check, skip else-if segnum check)
- OCaml: if awareness fails → maybe_fire_mp() → continue to do_firing_stuff, visibility==2 check, etc.

This means OCaml does MORE work for robots in AIM_STILL when awareness fails. `do_firing_stuff()` gets called, which could modify goal_state. The visibility==2 check might trigger (setting behavior or calling more effects).

